  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nWhile banner notifications tend to eventually arrive on iOS, there is no corresponding badge notification on the Status app icon. iOS has a more ephemeral approach to notifications compared to Android, so if the initial banner is missed, there is nothing left that reminds a user that there is unread content. Likewise, on macOS, there are no badge notifications either.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nNo badge notifications are displayed on iOS / macOS.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nBadge notification is displayed on the app icon until user opens the app and marks the messages as read.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nBanner notification arrives on iOS, but there is no badge applied to the app icon.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Put Status in background, e.g., go to home screen.\r\n2) Receive a message in Status\r\n3) Wait for notification to appear\r\n4) Unlock phone (back to home screen)\r\n5) Status app icon should display a badge notification.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: 1.20.2 (App Store) \r\n- Operating System: iOS 16.5.1\r\n\r\nSee https://developer.apple.com/documentation/usernotifications/unmutablenotificationcontent/1649875-badge",
